Real Madrid, Barcelona Win in La Liga; Bayern Moves Into First

-- B y   C h r i s t o p h e r   E l s e r
-- 
2011-12-03T21:09:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-03/real-madrid-barcelona-win-in-la-liga-bayern-moves-into-first.html
Real  Madrid  beat Sporting Gijon 3-0
and Barcelona won 5-0 at home against Levante to keep the top
two spots in Spanish soccerâ€™s La Liga.  Angel Di Maria, Cristiano Ronaldo and Marcelo scored for
Real, while Barcelona got two goals from Cesc Fabregas and one
each from Isaac Cuenca, Lionel Messi and Alexis Sanchez. Real
has a three-point lead and has played one fewer game than
Barcelona as the teams prepare to meet next week in Madrid for
the first Clasico of the season.  Racing Santander defeated Villarreal 1-0 with a Christian
Stuani goal that lifted his club out of last place.  In Germany,  Bayern Munich  went to the top of the table
after getting two goals each from Franck Ribery and  Arjen Robben 
to win 4-2 at Werder Bremen. Dortmund lost ground after a 1-1
tie with Borussia Moenchengladbach.  Kaiserslautern tied Hertha Berlin 1-1, and Freiburg also
drew 1-1 with Hanover. Wolfsburg and Mainz tied 2-2, and
Dortmund tied 1-1. Stuttgart drew 2-2 with Cologne. Yesterday,
 Bayer Leverkusen  beat Hoffenheim 2-0.  In France, Montpellier won 4-0 against Lorient to take a
five-point lead in Ligue 1, and Lille moved into second with a a
3-2 win at Ajaccio. Brest and Saint-Etienne drew 2-2, Dijon tied
0-0 with Sochaux and Evian beat Valenciennes 2-1.  To contact the reporter on this story:
